radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is enlarged and fluid-filled measuring up to 1 cm. Slightly increased density of the periappendiceal fat suggesting mild fat stranding. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenals, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, rectum, urinary bladder, and distal ureters show no abnormalities.
